Variation. The only other specimen collected, CAT 207 - 1 , was about 30 cm in length and branched twice. The polyps of the latter specimen were examined in detail and differed from those of the holotype only in having slightly smaller sclerites on the polyp body. The largest sclerites were 2.4 mm in length whereas on the larger holotype the largest body sclerites are about 2.5 mm in length (
Fig. 6
). But the smaller CAT 207 - 1 had a much larger array of smaller rods on the polyp body and the rods in the tentacles were much smaller than on the holotype .
